==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monesia
<hw>Mo*ne"sia</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Pharm.)</fld>
<def>The bark, or a vegetable extract brought in solid cakes from South
America and believed to be derived from the bark, of the tree
<spn>Chrysophyllum glycyphloeum</spn>. It is used as an alterative and
astringent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monesin</ent>⟦br⟧
